  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In classification context DT works through binary splitting to categorize data into multiple outcomes.",
    "The process begins with a single node and proceeds to split the training data into subgroups (nodes) according to the feature most correlated with the outcome variable 49, 50.",
    "Each subgroup is then further divided based on the feature most associated with the outcome variable within those subgroups.",
    "This process continues until all nodes become pure or are unable to be split further.",
    "The primary measures of node impurity/purity are typically Gini and entropy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
